BusinessTech hosted its Digital Banking conference at The Venue, Melrose Arch, on 5 March – and it was a sold-out event. The conference drew expert speakers from across the banking industry to share their insights into the future of digital finance in South Africa. This included Akash Dowra from Discovery Bank, who provided on the company’s first year of operation; expert insights from senior investment executive at Rand Merchant Investments, Dominique Collett; and a look at why Capitec decided to launch a new app at the start of the year, as told by the bank’s Roderick May. Fortinet country manager for South Africa, Paul Williams, highlighted the growing importance of intrusion prevention and endpoint security within the digital finance industry. The conference was hosted by The Money Show’s Bruce Whitfield. You can read more about what was said at the conference here: These security systems work overtime to ensure your transactions are safe
Here’s how many wealthy South Africans are living from payday to payday
Why Capitec launched a whole new banking app
This is how South Africa’s biggest financial companies are converging
M-Pesa wants to be more than just a mobile money service Delegates included many professionals and leaders within the South African banking and fintech sector, who were treated to excellent service at The Venue – including drinks, lunch and top-class facilities. Sponsors for the event included, Fortinet, Codehesion, Commvault, Winjit, and Onsite. If you missed out on this year’s Digital Bank Conference, here is a look at the event in photos. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-379589" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference.jpg" alt="" width="1390" height="927" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference.jpg 1390w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference-300x200.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference-768x512.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-379591" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference2.jpg" alt="" width="1390" height="927" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference2.jpg 1390w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference2-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/DigitalBankingConference2-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 